The financial crisis continues to impact on people in Greece this summer, as the country prepares to take its annual break this means families are struggling to feed their children during August.Are you a family or parent affected and using soup kitchens this summer? Or a community organisation or help centre trying to support families during the crisis in August? We're looking for your stories of selfhelp, as well as the real picture of the situation for families this summer across the country.Share your story with us via GuardianWitness – we'll feature a selection of submissions on guardian.co.uk.Though we'd like to hear from you, your security is most important. We recognise it may not always be safe to record or share your experiences – so please think about this when sending your content to GuardianWitness.